# Sentiment Analysis using NLP

## Project Overview

This project performs Sentiment Analysis on IMDB movie reviews using Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Machine Learning techniques. The model classifies reviews as Positive or Negative based on the review text.

---

## Objective

The main objective of this project is to:

- Analyze textual movie reviews
- Preprocess text data using NLP techniques
- Convert text into numerical features using TF-IDF
- Train a Machine Learning model for sentiment prediction

---

## Technologies Used

- Python
- Google Colab
- Pandas
- NumPy
- NLTK
- Scikit-learn

---

## Dataset

Dataset Used:
IMDB Movie Reviews Dataset

Dataset contains:
- Review text
- Sentiment label (positive/negative)

---

## Machine Learning Algorithm

- Multinomial Naive Bayes

---

## NLP Techniques Used

- Text Cleaning
- Lowercase Conversion
- Stopword Removal
- Stemming
- TF-IDF Vectorization

---

## Project Workflow

1. Import Libraries
2. Load Dataset
3. Preprocess Text Data
4. Convert Text into TF-IDF Vectors
5. Split Dataset into Training and Testing Sets
6. Train Naive Bayes Model
7. Predict Sentiment
8. Evaluate Model Accuracy

---

## Model Evaluation

The model is evaluated using:

- Accuracy Score
- Classification Report

Expected Accuracy:
Approximately 85% to 88%

---

## How to Run the Project

1. Open Google Colab
2. Upload the IMDB Dataset CSV file
3. Run all code sections step by step
4. Enter custom movie reviews for prediction

